        {
            "text": "Joob et al. reported on a dengue-like petechial rash in a COVID-19 patient from Thailand. 4 Recalcati 54 Table 1 . Most common systemic symptoms were fever (n=21/22; 95.5%), followed by cough (n=16; 72.7%), 73 headache (n=11; 50%), weakness (n=11; 50%), coryza (n=10; 45.5%), dyspnea (n=9; 40.9%), hyposmia 74 (n=4; 18.2%), hypogeusia (n=4; 18.2%), pharyngodynia (n=1; 4.5%), diarrhea (n=1; 4.5%), myalgia 75 (n=1; 4.5%). Death occurred in three (13.6%) patients. 76",
            "cite_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 90,
                    "end": 91,
                    "text": "4",
                    "ref_id": "BIBREF3"
                }
            ],
            "ref_spans": [
                {
                    "start": 105,
